        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="958" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.24/3–1346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-13T18:00:00-05:00">March 13, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Dept has notified Paraguayan representative of availability for their
                    purchase from surplus of military ground equipment for 1 Battalion of
                    Infantry.</p>
                <pb facs="1209" n="1191" xml:id="pg_1191"/>
                <p>Details concerning prices and terms to be arranged by Paraguayan representatives
                    directly with Foreign Liquidation Commission.</p>
                <p>Above equipment excludes some civilian items, particularly motor vehicles, not
                    now available in surplus.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
